1
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:13,367
<i>So that's why Jade,
who's also a bad person,</i>

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,600
<i> couldn't love you, too.</i>

3
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:16,833
<i>Because you're
a worthless person!</i>

4
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:18,233
<i> That's enough!</i>

5
00:00:18,367 --> 00:00:19,200
<i> She resigned.</i>

6
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> You're wedding is still on?</i>

7
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:21,800
<i> Of course!</i>

8
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,600
<i>I won't let your wedding happen.</i>

9
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:25,967
<i>Let's say that Logan
really did that to you.</i>

10
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,267
<i> Show me your proof.</i>

11
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,800
<i> I might believe you.</i>

12
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,700
<i> Mookie, no!</i>

13
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:32,433
<i> I feel so betrayed!</i>

14
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:35,067
<i> You didn't believe me,</i>

15
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:36,467
<i>and on top of that,
you disrespected me.</i>

16
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> And worse, you humiliated me!</i>

17
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,800
<i> I'm really sorry.</i>

18
00:01:18,033 --> 00:01:20,100
Wait.

19
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:21,300
I'll just take this call.

20
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,333
Oh, no.

21
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,867
Boss Logan is calling me.

22
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,900
Answer it. But don't tell him
we're together.

23
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:30,967
Okay, okay.

24
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:32,300
Hold on.

25
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:36,867
Hello, Boss?

26
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,433
Flor...

27
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:39,467
where's Emma?

28
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,800
<i> Boss, she's not with me.</i>

29
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,700
She's with you!

30
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,433
No one else knows
where she is aside from you.

31
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:48,867
So stop denying it!
Let me talk to her!

32
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,400
Okay, sure.

33
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:02,167
Hello, Logan?

34
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:05,633
Why are you looking for me?

35
00:02:06,867 --> 00:02:08,967
What do you need?

36
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:09,833
What the...

37
00:02:09,967 --> 00:02:11,033
Flor, what are you doing?

38
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:12,867
Come on, Boss Logan.

39
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,367
You're so stubborn.

40
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:17,267
I told you I didn't know
where she is.

41
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,467
We're not together.

42
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,333
<i> She just called me earlier.</i>

43
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:23,300
<i> She said she had resigned.</i>

44
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:27,633
Wait, I should be the one
asking you where she is.

45
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:30,533
Hello?

46
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,067
He hung up.

47
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:41,467
Where did she go?

48
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,900
So, what's your plan?

49
00:02:43,033 --> 00:02:44,133
Have you thought of a way

50
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:47,267
to prove that Jade and Logan
are working together?

51
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,000
I have.

52
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:51,433
The CCTV again.

53
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:55,033
We need to find footage
that shows their connivance.

54
00:02:55,167 --> 00:02:57,000
And we'll show it to Danilo.

55
00:02:58,133 --> 00:03:00,300
Yes, that's it! Right.

56
00:03:00,433 --> 00:03:02,267
I hope we find something.

57
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,167
Listen. I'll give you
my laptop's password.

58
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,867
Check all the CCTV footages.

59
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:19,400
Miss Ligaya,
I brought you some snacks.

60
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:24,233
Miss Ligaya, wake up.

61
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:30,033
Miss Ligaya?

62
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:32,433
Miss Ligaya!

63
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,367
Miss Ligaya!

64
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:46,000
Hey!

65
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:48,467
What are you doing?

66
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,667
Miss Ligaya, you scared me.

67
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,900
I dreamed it was shaking.

68
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,033
I thought there
was an earthquake.

69
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:56,300
And then I couldn't breathe.

70
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:59,333
It turns out you were the
one doing all sorts of things.

71
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,100
What's happening to me?

72
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:07,167
Why can't I feel my legs?

73
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,667
Why are they numb?

74
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,133
What's going on?

75
00:04:11,267 --> 00:04:14,533
The medicine that injected
into you last night

76
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:16,067
was an anesthetic.

77
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:16,967
What?

78
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,800
And she told me
to give you another dose today.

79
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:24,333
Are you really going to kill me?

80
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:28,667
I'm sorry, but...

81
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:29,833
Go ahead.

82
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:32,933
Do what you need to do.

83
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,667
Don't worry.
I won't get mad at you.

84
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:41,933
You're just doing
what your boss tells you. Right?

85
00:04:42,067 --> 00:04:43,233
Go ahead.

86
00:04:45,467 --> 00:04:47,233
Please forgive me, Miss Ligaya.

87
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,900
I just had to do it.

88
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,600
Do it quickly.

89
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:37,000
Dad?

90
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:40,033
- Mookie, dear.
- You're drinking again?

91
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:41,033
Yes.

92
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:48,467
Dad...

93
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,967
You know what, Dear?
I'm doing my best to be brave.

94
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:56,900
But the truth is...

95
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:02,767
the pain is unbearable.

96
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:09,700
What your mother did
to me is so painful.

97
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:15,467
I was so hurt.

98
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:21,167
What Emma did to me
was so painful.

99
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:25,633
To us, right?

100
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:28,667
Right?

101
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,600
You know what, Dad?

102
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:31,767
Me, too.

103
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:37,900
I'm just trying to focus
on finding grandmother.

104
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,333
So I won't think about mom.

105
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:48,533
But...

106
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,833
But deep inside...

107
00:06:54,233 --> 00:06:56,500
it's so painful.

108
00:06:59,267 --> 00:07:01,600
I'm in so much pain.

109
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:14,367
Maybe it's time for us to...

110
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:18,367
forget about your mom.

111
00:07:21,667 --> 00:07:27,367
Let's focus on building
our family...

112
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,100
with Jade.

113
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,967
You love her, too, right?

114
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:40,800
Your Mommy Jade loves us.

115
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,867
Mookie, after the wedding...

116
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,833
let's go to Cebu.

117
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,300
We'll look for your grandmother.

118
00:08:12,667 --> 00:08:13,633
Please, please.

119
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:17,033
I hope I can find a video
of Boss Logan and Jade.

120
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:20,267
Where is it?

121
00:08:21,533 --> 00:08:24,033
Gosh, there's really none!

122
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:26,667
What CCTV haven't I checked yet?

123
00:08:27,867 --> 00:08:31,267
The one at the parking lot!
Yes, that's right.

124
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,767
Parking.

125
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,333
Got you!

126
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:45,067
I caught you!

127
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:49,000
Wait, I should do this fast
before they catch me.

128
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:52,633
Come on. There you go. Let's go.

129
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,600
Got it!

130
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:03,733
Okay, okay.

131
00:09:03,867 --> 00:09:05,167
I haven't forgotten anything.

132
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,533
Boss Logan?

133
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:26,067
What are you doing here?

134
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:33,467
Emma hasn't given our sales
report for last month

135
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,067
to the accountant.

136
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,200
She's outside waiting for that.

137
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:39,600
Emma told me to get this
the last time she called.

138
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,267
<i> What?</i>

139
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,267
<i> Me?</i>

140
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,567
<i> You want me to check the CCTV?</i>

141
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:47,633
<i> Come on, Emma.</i>

142
00:09:47,767 --> 00:09:51,467
<i>What you want is too dangerous!</i>

143
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,500
<i> What if Marco catches me?</i>

144
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:55,867
<i> Or Boss Logan himself?</i>

145
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,933
<i> I'll be dead.</i>

146
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,100
<i>I've thought about that already,
Flor.</i>

147
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:00,067
<i> Let's do this.</i>

148
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,800
<i>Our accountant
will be at the bar.</i>

149
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:04,600
<i>She'll get the sales report
for last month.</i>

150
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:06,267
<i> I haven't given her that yet.</i>

151
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,533
<i> Print it.</i>

152
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,500
<i>If someone catches you
going through my laptop,</i>

153
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:12,867
<i>tell them I asked you to do it.</i>

154
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:26,700
Thank you.

155
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:31,867
Boss, what's the matter?

156
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,233
Where's Emma?

157
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:38,200
Boss, I don't know.

158
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:43,267
You know.

159
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:47,867
So tell me...

160
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,133
where is Emma?

161
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:54,100
-If not...
-If not, what will you do, Boss?

162
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:56,967
Are you going to fire me?

163
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,267
Okay.

164
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,933
I can't do anything
if that's what you want to do.

165
00:11:03,067 --> 00:11:05,300
But no matter how much
you pressure me,

166
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:09,700
I won't say anything because I
really don't know where Emma is.

167
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,533
Go ahead.

168
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:19,533
Give the report
to the accountant.

169
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:20,767
Okay.

170
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:21,767
Thank you, Boss.

171
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:24,267
Flor!

172
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:28,900
Yes, Boss?

173
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,033
Your money's sticking out
of your pocket.

174
00:11:37,167 --> 00:11:38,367
It might fall out.

175
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,367
Sorry. Thank you, Boss.

176
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,567
Emma!

177
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,767
Emma!

178
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:03,267
- Emma, Emma.
- Flor.

179
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,333
Here you go.

180
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:05,633
Here's the proof.

181
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:09,100
This will prove that Jade
and Boss Logan are in cahoots.

182
00:12:09,233 --> 00:12:11,000
- Thank you.
- Sure.

183
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,333
Go get your laptop. Hurry!

184
00:12:12,467 --> 00:12:14,000
Okay, I will.

185
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,300
There.

186
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,267
I got it.

187
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,900
Sit down.

188
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:28,700
Open it.

189
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,433
Flor, thank you so much.

190
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:56,200
I'm sorry for putting you
in danger.

191
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,200
Come on, it's okay.

192
00:12:58,333 --> 00:12:59,333
It's not a big deal.

193
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:10,500
Hello, Mom.

194
00:13:17,533 --> 00:13:20,633
I'm sorry I wasn't available
to take your call earlier.

195
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:23,000
I was taking a nap.

196
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:26,233
I'm still at work.
I'm looking after a...

197
00:13:26,367 --> 00:13:27,633
patient.

198
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,767
I can't go home yet.

199
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,933
I promise,
once I'm done with my work,

200
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:37,067
you're the first person
I'll visit.

201
00:13:40,733 --> 00:13:41,900
Don't be upset, Mom.

202
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:45,267
I can't just leave my job.

203
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,200
My boss is getting
married today.

204
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:50,833
I'm okay, Mom.

205
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:54,800
I'm in Artemis' warehouse
in District San Nicolas.

206
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:01,233
<i>Olive and Danilo are going
to get married today?</i>

207
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,967
Be safe, Mom.

208
00:14:04,033 --> 00:14:05,567
I'll see you when I get home.

209
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:07,667
Bye.

210
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,000
I love you.

211
00:14:41,433 --> 00:14:45,667
I can't believe it
that this is the day!

212
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:48,000
I'm getting married!

213
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,733
Is this really happening?

214
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:51,100
Astrid,

215
00:14:51,233 --> 00:14:52,767
can you slap me?

216
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:57,467
I want to know if this is real.

217
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:01,800
What are you doing?

218
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:04,033
You asked me to slap you.

219
00:15:05,167 --> 00:15:06,933
Are you serious?

220
00:15:07,067 --> 00:15:08,200
That was just...

221
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:14,033
maybe you really want
to slap me, don't you?

222
00:15:15,467 --> 00:15:16,300
Of course not.

223
00:15:16,433 --> 00:15:17,467
Come on.

224
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:21,067
You know me.
I always do what you say.

225
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,233
You know what?

226
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:25,933
If this is just
an ordinary day,

227
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:29,600
I would've slapped you
for being sarcastic.

228
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Got you!

229
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:37,500
You thought I was Olive, right?

230
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:41,033
Come on, Astrid!
This is just me.

231
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,167
I'm so excited for today.

232
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,533
The weather is perfect.

233
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,467
Everything is perfect.

234
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,567
The whole shebang is perfect.

235
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:52,400
Nothing will ever go wrong,

236
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:56,233
except for my perfect wedding.

237
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,800
- Come with me.
- Logan?

238
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:28,733
Stop!

239
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:30,033
I don't want to go with you!
Let me go!

240
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:31,800
- I'll take care of you.
- Let me go!

241
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:32,733
Don't make a noise!

242
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:34,867
Come on! Let go of me!

243
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:45,933
<i> Lord, please help me.</i>

244
00:18:48,533 --> 00:18:51,267
<i>Please help me
feel my legs again.</i>

245
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,267
<i> Please help me get up.</i>

246
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:58,500
Hey!

247
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:00,533
Why are you just staring
at the phone?

248
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:01,933
The number isn't in my contacts.

249
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,267
It might be a scammer.

250
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,033
Scammer?

251
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:07,367
Put it on loudspeaker.

252
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,433
Let's play with him.

253
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,300
Who knows?
It might be a foreigner!

254
00:20:11,433 --> 00:20:12,933
She likes foreigners.

255
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:14,233
For me?

256
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:17,533
For you. So that you can live
a better life, Kutsy. Right?

257
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,300
- Really?
- Yes.

258
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,267
It's ringing.

259
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,967
Go for it.

260
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:30,400
- I'll take it.
- Go on.

261
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:35,333
South Manila
Police District.

262
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:36,467
Hello?

263
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,300
Police?

264
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:40,867
Thank you.

265
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:41,800
Hello.

266
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:42,933
Hello, Ma'am.

267
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:46,433
I'm sorry, Ma'am.
I called the wrong number.

268
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:49,200
I'm Ligaya.

269
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:51,067
My name's Ligaya Joseco.

270
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:55,867
Ma'am, I need your help.
Please help me.

271
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,733
- Ligaya!
- Ligaya!

272
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:00,167
Ligaya, Ligaya! It's me, Kutsy!

273
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,367
You called the corect number!
This is my number!

274
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,733
This is me, Wiro.

275
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:07,733
Where are you?
What happened to you?

276
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:11,933
I'm in the Artemis
Pharmacy's warehouse.

277
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:13,933
Please save me. Help me.

278
00:21:14,067 --> 00:21:15,833
Artemis' warehouse?

279
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:18,367
Wait, wait.
What happened to you?

280
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,033
It's because...

281
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:21,767
Hello?

282
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,733
Hello?

283
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:24,833
Hello?

284
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:27,333
Ligaya?

285
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:28,333
Ligaya! Hello, hello!

286
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:29,633
Ligaya, BFF!

287
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:31,400
Ligaya!

288
00:21:31,533 --> 00:21:33,933
Kutsy, what happened?
Why did it get disconnected?

289
00:21:34,067 --> 00:21:35,533
The phone's dead.

290
00:21:35,667 --> 00:21:36,900
Dead batt.

291
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,433
- Auntie!
- Auntie!

292
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,533
- Charger!
- Charger!

293
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:45,500
- The charger's there!
- There it is, get it.

294
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:47,533
You're so slow, Auntie!

295
00:21:47,667 --> 00:21:49,567
My God, look what happened.

296
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:54,467
The whole shebang is perfect!

297
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:59,200
Nothing will ever go wrong,
but my perfect wedding.

298
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,133
I can't believe it!

299
00:22:04,633 --> 00:22:06,800
Baby girl!

300
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:10,167
Look at you, my sweetheart!

301
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,833
My Mookie is so beautiful.

302
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,900
Just like mommy.

303
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:16,700
Thank you, Mommy.

304
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:17,867
I'll just change my clothes.

305
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,767
Go ahead, get ready.

306
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,367
This is just the perfect day.

307
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,433
Jade, you need to change
your clothes now.

308
00:22:25,567 --> 00:22:26,600
Let me help you.

309
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:27,933
Okay.

310
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:29,267
Can I borrow my phone?

311
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,800
I just need to make
a quick phone call.

312
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,167
Thank you.

313
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:45,600
There!

314
00:22:45,733 --> 00:22:46,367
- There!
- There you go!

315
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:47,400
There it is. My God.

316
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:49,733
Okay, okay, okay.

317
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,033
Wait, wait.

318
00:22:51,167 --> 00:22:53,433
- How do I call Ligaya?
- Go to your...

319
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:54,433
go to your call history.

320
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,933
Okay, dial the recent number
on your list.

321
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,433
Right, right. That's it.

322
00:22:58,567 --> 00:22:59,567
Yes.

323
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,467
Wait a minute.

324
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,533
- There.
- There it is.

325
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,900
It's busy.

326
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,533
Maybe she called someone else.

327
00:23:13,667 --> 00:23:15,467
No, call her again.

328
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,700
Okay.

329
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:18,733
Please hurry up.

330
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:21,133
The one guarding me
might wake up anytime.

331
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:23,000
I just escaped him.

332
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:24,867
You escaped?

333
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,633
Monster.

334
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:35,667
You're a monster, Olive.

335
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:36,967
You know...

336
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:38,700
I will send you to jail.

337
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:42,233
I'll make sure you rot in jail.

338
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:43,900
Remember that!

339
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:50,867
She can't escape.

340
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:00,933
Jade, where are you going?

341
00:24:01,067 --> 00:24:02,633
I just need to take care
of something.

342
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:04,533
I'll be right back.

343
00:24:04,667 --> 00:24:06,967
Jade!

344
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,000
Give me that!

345
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:11,567
Come on!

346
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:12,667
Go over there!

347
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:16,100
Get in. Get in!

348
00:24:19,867 --> 00:24:21,800
What are you doing?
Where are you taking me?

349
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:30,500
I won't let you do that!

350
00:24:30,633 --> 00:24:32,433
He needs to get married to Jade.

351
00:24:32,567 --> 00:24:33,700
So you'll forget about him.

352
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:36,500
It will never happen
even if they get married!

353
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:38,567
We will never be together!

354
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,333
Well, believe me,

355
00:24:40,467 --> 00:24:42,233
we'll be together.

356
00:24:42,367 --> 00:24:43,367
Are you going to force me?

357
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,600
No,

358
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:47,767
I will love you,
and I will serve you.

359
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:50,800
I'll do everything to open
your heart and love me.

360
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:52,467
So you'll forget about Danilo

361
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,400
and focus all your attention
on me.

362
00:24:55,533 --> 00:24:58,300
You can't force my heart
to love you.

363
00:24:58,433 --> 00:25:00,200
Then I'll teach you...

364
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:01,667
until you learn.

365
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:05,233
Danilo is the only one I love.
So please leave me alone!

366
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,600
Help! Help!

367
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:12,500
- Help!
- Come here!

368
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:13,667
Come here!

369
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,100
- Let me go!
- What's your problem?

370
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:17,533
You're only mine!

371
00:25:17,667 --> 00:25:19,767
I will never be yours!

372
00:25:20,867 --> 00:25:22,767
Come here! You're so stubborn!

373
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:32,233
Darn this life!

374
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:35,733
All the women in my life
don't want me.

375
00:25:37,067 --> 00:25:38,000
So,

376
00:25:38,133 --> 00:25:39,900
I will not let this
happen to me.

377
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,200
You're only mine.

378
00:25:53,467 --> 00:25:57,267
Jade, where are you?
Why aren't you answering?

379
00:26:00,933 --> 00:26:05,533
Jade, where did you go?
Oh, come on.

380
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:11,433
Excuse me.

381
00:26:11,567 --> 00:26:13,033
What's going on?

382
00:26:13,167 --> 00:26:16,367
Jade left all of a sudden.
I don't know where she went.

383
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,433
I'll go for now.
I'll look for her.

384
00:26:19,567 --> 00:26:21,300
Please take care of Mookie,
okay?

385
00:26:21,433 --> 00:26:22,500
I'm leaving, bye.

386
00:26:22,633 --> 00:26:24,833
- Okay.
- Take care of everything.

387
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,667
There you go!
It's already ringing!

388
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:29,933
It's ringing!

389
00:26:30,067 --> 00:26:30,967
Hurry up.

390
00:26:35,633 --> 00:26:37,033
Hello, Kutsy?

391
00:26:37,167 --> 00:26:39,567
- Is it you, Kutsy?
- Yes! Ligaya, it's me!

392
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:42,000
It's Kutsy!
We'll come and get you!

393
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:43,700
Where are you?

394
00:26:43,833 --> 00:26:44,733
Which warehouse is it?

395
00:26:44,867 --> 00:26:46,067
<i> I'm here...</i>

396
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,700
at District...

397
00:26:52,133 --> 00:26:54,133
<i> - Hello?
-</i> She's gone again!

398
00:26:54,267 --> 00:26:56,633
- She's gone again!
- BFF!

399
00:27:03,967 --> 00:27:06,000
My grandmother is in danger!

400
00:27:06,133 --> 00:27:06,867
What?

401
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,167
Yes! That's why we need to go!

402
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:12,100
I wish you had just melted
inside my womb

403
00:27:12,233 --> 00:27:14,700
when I was pregnant
with you and Jade.

404
00:27:14,833 --> 00:27:19,667
I regret bringing you
into this world.

405
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,767
Bury her, Caloy!

406
00:27:23,900 --> 00:27:25,267
You want us to push through
with the wedding

407
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:27,500
- even without Mookie?
- Of course, Love!

408
00:27:27,633 --> 00:27:30,533
Love, I'm sure Mookie
will understand.

409
00:27:30,667 --> 00:27:32,100
She'll just follow.

410
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:43,000
Grandmother!
